Description: The Flight into Egypt; the Holy Family and a donkey emerge from a dense wood at left, a kneeling angel offers the Christ child a basket of fruit, two putti float overhead and drop flowers, a palm tree beyond; after Jan Thomas. 1650 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Frans van den Wyngaerde
Curator's comments: For another impression see S.5608. The paper is heavily foxed and the margins are damaged.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (2.II)
Schneevoogt 1873 / Catalogue des estampes gravées d'après P.P.Rubens (27.133) (describes an impression touched by Rubens)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Hans Sloane (with Philipe's oval stamp with the initials missing, but with Sloane stamp of the 1870s)
